Wilkins Charisia, 1, 732f.‚ gives these as added to by 1116 successor, Simon de Watton (1257-1267), but the coincidences are confined to the first half of the Norwich Statutes. The order of the provisions is not always the same but otherwise the Norwich Statutes account for a considerable proportion of our MS. down to nearly the end of its p. 35. One or two things are in other statutas, eg. Langton's, Otho's, William de Kirkham's, bp of Durham (1240-1260), and &Valter de Cantelulie's, bp of Worcester (1237-1266).
